= Sections

Sections organize your document into a hierarchical structure with headings and navigation.

== Overview

Sections provide the structural backbone of your document, creating a clear hierarchy that helps readers navigate and understand the content organization.

== Section Features

This category includes the following section-related features:

* *Document Header* - Title, author, revision, and document attributes
* *Section Headings* - Hierarchical headings from level 1 to level 5
* *Nested Sections* - Creating complex document structures
* *Section IDs* - Anchor points and cross-referencing

== Usage

Sections create the document outline and enable features like table of contents and cross-referencing. Click on any feature above to see examples and learn how to structure your documents.

